A 65 years old hunter, Uchechukwu Nweke, has killed his wife, son and shot himself yesterday in Amunike community, Awka North Council of Anambra State. It was gathered that Nweke allegedly shot his wife, Patricia Nweke (55) and his son named Obinna Nweke (29) with a single barrel gun and also burnt his house. He was said to have equally shot himself using the same gun in a circumstances yet to be ascertained. Confirming the incident, the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) in Anambra State, CSP Haruna Mohammed, said the command received the report from the vigilante chairman, Amunike community yesterday, January 28, 2021. In a statement released yesterday, CSP Haruna Mohammed, said, “there was a report from the vigilante chairman Amunike community in Awka North LGA of Anambra State that on the same date at about 3:am, a hunter one Uchechukwu Nweke ‘m’ aged 65 years of same address allegedly shot his wife Patricia Nweke ‘f’ aged 55 years with a single barrel gun and also burnt his house along with his son named Obinna Nweke aged 29 years in a circumstances yet to be ascertained. Suspect equally shot himself using the same gun. “Police detectives attached to Achalla police station visited the scene and rushed victims to Uche Hospital Isuanocha for medical attention where all the three victims were certified dead by a medical doctor on arrival.” He said corpses of the victims were deposited at the hospital’s morgue for autopsy, adding that investigation is ongoing to ascertain circumstances surrounding the incident. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .